te and reduced line\nlists, respectively, corresponding to a reduced observing efficiency of a\nfactor 4.3 and 1.2. The reduced line list outperforms the complete line list in\nrecovering the actual VO signal in the M-dwarf spectra by about a factor of\n1.8. Neither line list results in a VO detection in WASP-121b. Injection tests\nshow that with the reduced efficiency of the line lists, the potential signal\nas seen at low resolution is not detectable in these data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Mar 2022 18:34:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-25"}
